HEADWORD: Sanctum
<hw>Sanc"tum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., p. p. of
<ets>sancire</ets> to consecrate.]</ety> <def>A sacred place; hence, a
place of retreat; a room reserved for personal use; <as>as, an editor's
<ex>sanctum</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs>\'d8<col><b>Sanctum sanctorum</b></col> <ety>[L.]</ety>, <cd>the
Holy of Holies; the most holy place, as in the Jewish
temple.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sanctus</ent>⟦br⟧
